sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1838008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part features the glucose inducible promoter BBa_K861171 combined via 3A assembly with a blue chromoprotein+RBS part (BBa_K1073021). This part is meant to be placed into the tri-color glucose detection composite part in order to contribute increasing levels of blue protein as glucose concentration rises.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Connor McFadden
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Inducible was very small so we had to synthesize over using 3A assembly. I would recommend finding some way to extend the length of one part or circumvent using parts <150 bp for 3A if a similar design is required for your new part/project.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a subpart of BBa_K107320. It does not include the promoter, if the user wants to add an e.g. inducable or stronger/weaker promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a combination of BBa_B0032 and BBa_K864401, which were taken from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pcar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Pcar, synthetic promoter repressed by CRP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a promoter designed for the Eschaerichia coli . It includes the CRP-binding site and the RNA polymerase-binding site which have a overlap of several base pairs.So because of the steric hindrance between CRP and RNA polymerase,gene downstream of the promoter will be repressed at high concentration of CRP.In the cells ,low glucose concentration results in increased activity by adenylate cyclase. cAMP binds to the cAMP receptor protein, which, in its bound form, is able to bind tightly to the specific DNA site in the promoter and repress the gene downstream.On the contrary,high glucose concentration will result in the expression of the promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
